thread.section_title: Breaking news on air travel - breakingnews.com
thread.title: Editor's note: Moments after Malaysian Prime Minister Najib Razak said experts had conclusively confirmed that wing debris found on Reunion Island is from the MH370, the Paris prosecutor's office hedged, saying there was 'strong supposition' that the debris was from the missing flight and that a complete analysis would begin on Thursday. The debris found includes a wing piece, known as a flaperon, and a suitcase. - Jillian
